the red bull arena (german pronunciation: [ʁɛt ˈbʊl ʔaˌʁeːnaː] , formerly zentralstadion [tsɛnˈtʁaːlˌʃtaːdi̯ɔn] ), located in leipzig, saxony, germany, is a football facility in the former east germany. it is the largest football stadium in the former east germany and has also hosted music concerts as well as football. it is currently the home stadium for first-division club rb leipzig but various leipzig football teams have used the stadium as a home stadium, including vfb leipzig (precursor to 1. fc lokomotive leipzig) at various points in the 20th century (including large-scale european matches in the 1970s and domestic football in the 1990s).